  m_Name: Story 5
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  chapter: 5
  title: Balance In The Sky
  story: 'With the cargo airship fixed, you fly toward the Sky Fortress. The trip
    starts smoothly, but suddenly the cargo airship tilts to one side. Cargo slides
    across the floor, the engines shake, and the cargo airship begins to lose balance.
    The load needs to be centered again because the center of mass has moved, making
    the cargo airship unstable. To save it, you must act fast and understand how
    weight and movement affect balance.


    Each time you move a heavy crate, the
    cargo airship responds. If the weight is on one side, the cargo airship leans;
    when the weight is centered, it becomes steady again. You start to learn how
    the center of mass controls balance and how momentum causes the cargo airship
    to slide or tilt. Slowly, you put each object back in a safer position.


    After
    you fix the cargo arrangement, the cargo airship becomes stable again. By understanding
    balance and momentum, you are ready to continue your journey.'
